COLOUR (
Fig. 13F
). Dorsum generally brownish grey. Frons and vertex pale yellowish, eyes blackish brown. Pronotum greyish brown. Hemelytron with greyish background. Clavus with brown punctures near anterior margin. Corium with a broad transverse dark brown mark in the middle. Membrane generally dark brown, more hyaline apically. Venter of thorax and abdomen greyish brown and legs pale yellow or nearly whitish.
